HTTP Status Codes
Every response includes a status code.
200 OK
Everything worked.

201 Created
A new resource was successfully created.
Usually returned after POST.

400 Bad Request
Client sent invalid data.
Example
Age = "abc"

404 Not Found
Resource doesn't exist.
Example
GET /employees/999
when employee 999 isn't in the database.

500 Internal Server Error
Something went wrong inside the server.
Usually a bug in the application.

@PathVariable → Reads data from the URL.
@RequestBody → Reads data from the HTTP Body.